<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef2bbb6e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2009aa–9"><num value="2009aa–9">§ 2009aa–9.</num><heading> Consent of States</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this subchapter requires any State to engage in or accept any program under this subchapter without the consent of the State.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef2bbb6f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/87/128/tIII/s382J">Pub. L. 87–128, title III, § 382J</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/554/s1/a/4/dB/tV/s503">Pub. L. 106–554, § 1(a)(4) [div. B, title V, § 503]</ref>, <date date="2000-12-21">Dec. 21, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/2763">114 Stat. 2763</ref>, 2763A–280.)</sourceCredit>
